cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel approach for improving the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) on computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) for sequential attention, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmarks for camera localization and scene classification, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
